article.description: Evan Boudreaux scored 26 points on 10-for-15 shooting and gathered 13 rebounds as Dartmouth defeated Pennsylvania 72-64 Friday night.
article.headline: Boudreaux leads Dartmouth past Pennsylvania 72-64
article.story: HANOVER, N.H. -- Evan Boudreaux scored 26 points on 10-for-15 shooting and gathered 13 rebounds as Dartmouth defeated Pennsylvania 72-64 Friday night. Boudreaux was a point off his career high, which he set Feb. 5 against the Quakers. Taylor Johnson added 13 points and Connor Boehm chipped in 10 points and eight boards for Dartmouth (10-17, 4-9 Ivy League). Max Rothschild's jumper with 9:21 before halftime put the Quakers up 19-18. But Dartmouth proceeded to outscore Pennsylvania 22-10 to close the half and take a 40-29 lead at the break. Mike Fleming's layup put Dartmouth up 50-37 with 15:23 to play. Rothschild hit a 3 to cut the deficit to 56-50 seven minutes later. Darnell Foreman made two free throws to cut Dartmouth's lead to five with 1:12 left but Penn couldn't get closer. Rothschild tied his career high with 18 points for the Quakers (11-15, 5-7) on 7-for-9 shooting.
